cs.SI, cs.IR, cs.SD, cs.DL, cs.CY 

This paper deals with the analysis of networks of Wikipedia editions to determine the ranking of universities. It uses algorithms like PageRank and CheiRank to determine the ranking of universities. It also uses the reduced Google matrix algorithm to determine the interactions between leading universities on a scale of ten centuries. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Additionally, the paper deals with data analysis and algorithms, which could fall under sub-categories like cs.SD (Software Development), cs.DL (Digital Libraries), and cs.CY (Computers and Society).
